      • convert

        public FeatureType convert(FeatureDefn featureDefn,
                  String defaultGeometryField)
                    throws GeometryTypeNotSupportedException,
                           GeometryTypeNotValidException
        Converts FeatureDefn to FeatureType and sets default geometry field to created FeatureType.
        Parameters:
        featureDefn - OGR definition to be converted
        defaultGeometryField - Default geometry field. If it is not founded, this method will take the first geometry field.
        Returns:
        FeatureType Feature type equivalent
        Throws:
        GeometryTypeNotSupportedException - If there are problems parsing OGR geometry
        GeometryTypeNotValidException - If type of OGR Geometry is not supported

      • convert

        public org.gdal.ogr.Feature convert(FeatureDefn layerDefn,
                           org.gdal.ogr.Feature feature)
        Convert OGR Feature to another OGR Feature. This method take into account only FeatureDefn fields to create new feature. This method is useful when OGR Layer is copied to new DataSource.
        Parameters:
        layerDefn - Definition of new feature
        feature - OGR feature to be converted
        Returns:
        Fixed feature
